Creates a new symbolic link on the filesystem.

The `link` path will be a symbolic link pointing to the `original` path.

# Examples

```no_run
use std::os::unix::fs;

fn main() -> std::io::Result<()> {
    fs::symlink("a.txt", "b.txt")?;
    Ok(())
}
```
